name: Pioneer Abnormalities
description:
Amateur Assassins' first release, a ten track CD/EP featuring songs thrown together in preparation for their first gig. Four piece punk influences sitting alongside solo bedroom edit work. 

Stoke Sounds  
"First track Morphine Pupils initially reminiscent of industrial electronica. We are soon lead back into 
more familiar clean, jazz picking and anaphylactic vocal stylings on tracks such as Cyanide Sweet Shenanigans and 
Signed, Served and Sealed but crucially this is tempered by the moody instrumentalism of Dinosaur and others." 

Collective Zine 
"It takes the brash, twisted structures of The Jesus Lizard, combines it with twangy, minimal post-punk like 
Gang Of Four, and fronts it with an agonising, torturous vocalist, like if Guy Picciotto, Iggy Pop and 
Cedric Bixler were to merge into one single being and Quantum Leap into the body of Pee Wee Herman just 
as he is filming his new picture, Pee Wee On Fire." 

Tracklisting;

Morphine Pupils
Cyanide Sweet Shenanigans
One Fingered Dentist
Little Miss Carriage
Dinosaur
Signed, Severed and Sealed
Insomniacs Wet Dream
I Will Crucify You
The Human Clock Strikes Again
I Like Being Dead In Tetris

name: 14 Songs To Derail Your Zen
description: First release from Owd Ear Recordings, six people in one basement recording under various nonsensical guises. Featuring folk blues, electronica/dubstep, 60's pop and other random stylistic twists and turns. Lo- fi kaleidoscopic ambition with members of Tribal Brides of the Amazon, Pig Eyed Bandits and Amateur Assassins all implicated.
